The special handling for PHI nodes in `hoistInsertPoint` seems to be the culprit. Removing it should fix the issue, as the generic instruction handling path should be sufficient and correct.

I will remove the special case for `PHINode` in `hoistInsertPoint`.

```cpp
// In BoUpSLP::hoistInsertPoint
    // If the operand is a PHI node, it is only available in the scope of its
    // parent basic block.
    if (auto *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(I)) {
      InsertBlock = DT.findNearestCommonDominator(InsertBlock, PN->getParent());
      continue;
    }
```
